summaries.short: Season Two Finale. An old dog reflects on life; rats Phil and Mike face an unknown future as high school ends.
summaries.full: Season Two Finale. An old dog reflects on her life and doles out some sage advice. As high school graduation approaches, rat teens Phil and Mike consider what comes next, as their paths appear to be going separate ways.

summaries.short: Season Three Premiere. Two rats search for their missing car, as they contemplate their place in a New York City without humans.
summaries.full: Season Three Premiere. Three years after the green bomb wiped out humans in New York, rats Phil and Mike traverse the city following a wild, drunken night, searching for a missing car and encountering multiple species and terrors along the way.

summaries.short: The food chain is explored through three interconnected stories involving worms, bluebird chicks and two generations of opossums.
summaries.full: In this interconnected exploration of the urban food chain, two ends of a worm search for love and independence, a pair of newly-hatched bluebirds fight for survival, and an opossum father and son butt heads over the reality of being predators.

summaries.short: The heroic saga of a diminutive, but fiercely heroic bird who makes his way to Pigeon Heights, where he is tasked with saving the day.
summaries.full: The heroic saga of a diminutive, but fiercely heroic bird, Wallet, who leaves his home after tragedy strikes, makes his way to Pigeon Heights, where he becomes the right-hand man to recently crowned Pigeon King Phil, and is tasked with saving the day when terrorists take over a bar mitzvah.
